# Pydantic Schema Conventions

## File Organization

```
app/schemas/
  entity.py        # EntityCreate, EntityUpdate, EntityResponse
  edge.py          # EdgeCreate, EdgeResponse
  item.py          # ItemCreate, ItemResponse
  group.py         # GroupCreate, GroupResponse, GroupConfig
  data_entity.py   # DataEntityCreate, SourceInfo, EntryAppend, DataEntityRead
  user.py          # UserCreate, UserResponse, TokenPayload
```

## Naming Pattern

- `{Model}Create` — POST request body
- `{Model}Update` — PUT/PATCH request body (all fields optional)
- `{Model}Response` — API response shape

```python
class EntityCreate(BaseModel):
    content_type: Literal["markdown", "video", "audio"]
    title: str = Field(min_length=1, max_length=255)
    body: str | None = None
    url: HttpUrl | None = None

class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)

    id: str
    content_type: str
    title: str
    created_by: str
    created_at: datetime
```

## Validation

- Use `Field()` constraints (`min_length`, `ge`, `le`, `pattern`) over custom validators where possible.
- Custom validators use `@field_validator` — never `@root_validator` (use `@model_validator` in v2).
- All response models set `model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)` for ORM compatibility.
